festival.introText:

faqs.question: When is Detonate Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Detonate Festival returns to Colwick Country Park on Saturday 10th June 2023.

faqs.question: How much are Detonate Festival tickets?
faqs.answer: Tickets are not yet on sale but you can be the first to know when tickets do go on sale by signing up to a reminder above.

faqs.question: How to get to Detonate Festival?
faqs.answer:
By car

If you are coming from the north – follow the A60 or A612
If you are coming from the south – follow the A60 and A453
If you are coming from the east or west – follow the A52

Once you reach Nottingham, follow the brown signs or yellow park & ride signs to the Racecourse.

By bus

The nearest bus routes from the city centre is the number 44, which departs from King Street, or the Link 2 (yellow Park & Ride) which stops on Parliament Street and Collins Street.

By rail

Nottingham Midland Station is very close to the city centre, and so only around two miles from the Racecourse. There is a taxi rank at the station and it will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to reach the Racecourse. For details of train times please click www.nationalrail.co.uk

faqs.question: Where is Detonate Festival?
faqs.answer: Detonate Festival is located in Colwick Country Park, Nottingham which is around a 15 minute drive from Nottingham city centre. It takes about 20 minutes from the city centre by bus, metrolink or car. The postcode is NG2 4BE.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: What's included with a Detonate VIP ticket
faqs.answer:
A Detonate Festival VIP ticket includes:

 

- VIP fast track entrance
- Exclusive access to VIP island & water edge bar
- Fast track VIP service at all main bars
- Posh loos
- Deck chairs and seating area

faqs.question: What are the entry times to Detonate Festival?
faqs.answer:
Starts: 11:00am
Last Entry: 4:00pm 

End time: 11:00pm

faqs.question: Does Detonate Festival have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Detonate Festival is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed. It is however close to the City Centre so there is plenty of alternative accommodation to choose from.

faqs.question: Does Detonate Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Detonate Festival. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Detonate Festival?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Detonate Festival. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of Detonate Festival 2019
reviewsDisplayFour.body: This was my 2nd visit to Detonate, I went back when it was held at the Racecourse. Ques was good, didn't take long at all, I didn't think the prices were to bad at all. Even though we had lots of rain i thought the ground was decent, and loved the set up. Couple of things I thought could be better, the VIP area was poor, and twice I walked in with no one on the barrier so it was rammed at the bar and toilets. I thought there could have been other VIP loos scattered about. I thought the let down was the volume of music, you could have a full conversation in the Bigtop which was playing DnB, It missed that "umph" on alot of stages. Heard a few people say it was down to restrictions, but at an event like that i think it needed to be louder. All in all an amazing day, staff awesome, well organised and planned!
